								<RECORD id="0-0-0-3998" number="4791" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Certificate of occupancy.</CHARFORMAT> An amended certificate of occupancy need not be obtained in order to occupy an otherwise lawful apartment for use as a student apartment.</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-3999" number="4792" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(f)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Records.</CHARFORMAT> The college or university shall maintain records at the building that contains any student apartment, identifying the unit numbers of student apartments, the maximum number of students housed in each such unit, whether the students are post-graduate or are permitted to be undergraduate, and where applicable, whether the apartment was first occupied as a student apartment prior to July 1, 2009. Such records shall be available for inspection by the Department, the Fire Department, and the Department of Housing Preservation and Development. The college or university may be required to produce further records to substantiate compliance with this section.</PARA>
